21_28	0.15404074	And federal wildlife biologists define a wolf ``population'' as at least two wild breeding pairs that raise at least two young in an area for the previous two years.
21_29	0.19282263	There is no evidence that a naturally occurring wolf population existed in Yellowstone or central Idaho prior to the introduction of the gray wolves.
21_30	0.14651771	Therefore, concluded the appellate court, on that question, the Department of the Interior did not violate the Endangered Species Act.
